<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                        <head><persName type="from">Lord Lyons</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-02-06"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 6, 1863.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have this afternoon had the honor to
                            receive your note of yesterday’s date respecting the blockade of the
                            port of Galveston, in Texas.</p>
                        <p>In acknowledging the receipt of your communication, I take the
                            opportunity of repeating to you the assurance of the high consideration
                            with which I am, sir, your most obedient, humble servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>LYONS.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>